    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/vad-cou2-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD hemolysis model demonstrates sufficient predictive capability for the VAD context of use. Validation activities against the FDA generic pump geometry provide adequate evidence of model performance. The Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification framework addresses geometric variability and supports confidence in the hemolysis predictions across the operating envelope. The assessment team finds the achieved credibility levels acceptable for the intended regulatory submission.",
